Copilot said: Great! To host your landing page, you

Great! To host your landing page, you have several options—here are the easiest and most popular approaches:

1. GitHub Pages (Free & Reliable)

Best for: Static HTML like yours, no backend needed, custom domain possible.

Steps:

  1. Create a GitHub Repo:
    Name it e.g. startup-sprint-101-landing.
  2. Upload Your Files:
    Add your HTML file, banner.jpg, and faculty.jpg to the root of the repo.
  3. Enable GitHub Pages:
    • Go to the repo → Settings → Pages.
    • Select main branch and / (root) directory.
    • Save.
      GitHub will provide a URL like:
      https://<your-username>.github.io/startup-sprint-101-landing/
  4. Done!
    Your site will be live at that URL.

2. Netlify (Super Easy, Drag-n-Drop or Git Integration)

Best for: Drag-and-drop deployment, custom domains, more features.

Steps:

  • Go to Netlify Drop
  • Drag your folder (with HTML + images inside) onto the window.
  • Netlify gives you a live URL instantly.

Or, connect your GitHub repo for auto-deployment.

3. Vercel (Modern, Git Integration)

Best for: Git-based deployments, custom domains, fast CDN.

Steps:

  • Go to Vercel
  • Import your repo or deploy manually.
  • Follow instructions, your site is live in seconds.

4. Google Drive (Quick & Dirty for Internal Use)

  • Not recommended for public-facing sites, but you can host static HTML by uploading and sharing the folder.

Want me to auto-generate the GitHub repo structure for you?

If yes, I can:

  • Create a README.md
  • Place your HTML and image "stubs"
  • Give you the upload instructions for images

Just let me know!

Or, if you want step-by-step commands for one of the above methods, tell me your preference (GitHub Pages, Netlify, Vercel, etc.), and I’ll walk you through it with screenshots and exact commands if needed.
